{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CyV8RpdZLtWDQr4ZM3yMqP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is in order. Here's a summary of what was done and why:\n\n**Root causes found:**\n\n1. **Capacity change**: `es-transform-config` had `node.roles: [ ingest ]` — the `transform` role had been removed, reducing the cluster's transform capacity. Fixed by patching the configmap back to `[ ingest, transform ]` and rolling the StatefulSet.\n\n2. **Stale checkpoint**: The transform was stuck at checkpoint 1 with 2 unprocessed documents (`seed-new-1`, `seed-new-2`) that had `@timestamp` values in January 2026 — well before the sync's `time_upper_bound` of June 2026. In continuous transform mode, time-based sync only searches for documents with timestamps *after* the last upper bound, so those past-dated docs could never be picked up without a reset.\n\n**Actions taken (all via transform APIs):**\n1. `POST /_transform/events-by-service/_stop?force=true` — stopped the stuck transform\n2. `POST /_transform/events-by-service/_reset` — cleared internal checkpoint state (does not touch destination index)\n3. `POST /_transform/events-by-service/_start` — started fresh; initial batch processed all 5 source docs\n\n**Final state:**\n- Transform: `started`, checkpoint 1, health `green`\n- Destination `app-events-rollup`: `api: 3`, `web: 2` (all 5 source docs now aggregated correctly)\n- Elastic password `elasticpass` confirmed working against HTTPS"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":652,"cache_read_input_tokens":76205,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":652},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76f3b3ad-df3a-4830-a932-a070652945d9","uuid":"dd74317d-a994-41f1-8bcb-5